.th HEADER VII "June 1979"
.sh NAME
header \*- obtain the header of a picture
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd header
(file,hbuf)
.s3
char *file
.br
int hbuf[6]
.sh DESCRIPTION
.lp +9 9
file	CXAP picture file
.lp +9 9
hbuf	storage for header information
.i0
.s3
.it Header
reads the first 12 bytes of
.it file
into
.it hbuf.
.it File
is closed before a return is made.
.s3
The description of
.it hbuf
is:
.br
.nf
.in 10
.s3
hubf[0] = unused,
hbuf[1] = # columns in picture,
hubf[2] = unused,
hbuf[3] = # rows in picture,
hubf[4] = unused,
hbuf[5] = byte size of picture.
.fi
.i0
.s3
Function value is -1 on error and +1 on success.
